    <p class="text-gray-300">Definition 5. We say the relation generator R has hard decisional problems if there are two polynomial time algorithms Yes and No such that for (R, z) ← R(1&lt;sup&gt;λ&lt;/sup&gt; ) we have Yes(R) → (φ, w) ∈ R and No(R) → φ /∈ L&lt;sup&gt;R&lt;/sup&gt; with overwhelming probability, and for all non-uniform polynomial time distinguishers A</p>

